==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parapeptone
<hw>Par`a*pep"tone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>peptone</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Phisiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A proteinaceous body formed in small quantity by the
peptic digestion of proteids. It can be converted into peptone by
pancreatic juice, but not by gastric juice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parapet</ent>⟦br⟧
